Document Viewer Debug Log
=========================
Test Time: 2025-06-17 15:07
Purpose: Debug why document viewer returns 404 error

Issue:
- When clicking a document in project view, get "Error: Failed to get document URL: 404"
- Backend has the endpoint: GET /documents/{document_id}/download-url
- Frontend correctly calls getDocumentDownloadUrl with document ID

Possible Causes:
1. Document ID format issue (UUID parsing)
2. User permission issue (document belongs to different user)
3. Document marked as inactive
4. S3 configuration issue

Debug Steps:
1. The frontend navigates to /document-viewer/{document.id}
2. The page component calls getDocumentDownloadUrl(documentId)
3. This makes a request to /api/documents/{documentId}/download-url
4. Backend returns 404

Need to check:
1. If the document ID is valid
2. If the document exists in the database
3. If the user has permission to access it
4. Backend logs for the actual error